humanMachineDialogue.author: Memory Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: The report mentions 'Metastases carcinomatosae in lymphonodis (No IX/XV)'. This indicates that out of the fifteen assessed lymph nodes, nine had metastases. This corresponds to N2 according to Rule 14: N2 indicates metastases in 4 to 9 axillary lymph nodes.

humanMachineDialogue.author: ZS Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: The patient has metastatic carcinoma in 9 out of 15 (IX/XV) axillary lymph nodes, which indicates a pathologic N stage of N2. This is based on the American Joint Committee on Cancer (AJCC) staging system for breast cancer, where N1 represents metastasis in 1-3 axillary lymph nodes, N2 represents metastasis in 4-9 axillary lymph nodes, and N3 represents metastasis in 10 or more axillary lymph nodes.
